Argentine Stocks: Banco Hipotecario and Pampa Energia Advance

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-05-02T16:37:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/argentine-stocks-banco-hipotecario-and-pampa-energia-advance.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:02 p.m. New York time.  The Merval Index rose 0.7 percent to 3,428.09.  Banco Hipotecario SA (BHIP)   gained 1.2 percent to 2.60
pesos, its third day of gains. Argentine banks posted a 42
percent increase in loans to companies in the first quarter from
a year earlier, the nationâ€™s central bank said in an April 29
report.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   increased 1.6 percent to 16.15
pesos.  Pampa Energia SA (PAMP)   rose 2.7 percent to 2.67 pesos,
its fourth day of gains. The Argentine energy holding company is
benefiting from the announcement by Transportadora de Gas del
Sur SA on April 29 that it plans to pay 976 million pesos in
dividends, Juan Jose Vasquez, an analyst at Bull Market Brokers
in  Buenos Aires , said in a telephone interview. Pampa indirectly
controls TGS.  To contact the reporter on this story:
